324.400.  Definitions. — As used in sections 324.400 to 324.439, the following terms mean:
  (1)  "Council", the interior design council created in section 324.406;
  (2)  "Division", the division of professional registration;
  (3)  "Registered interior designer", a design professional who provides services including preparation of documents and specifications relative to nonload-bearing interior construction, furniture, finishes, fixtures and equipment and who meets the criteria of education, experience and examination as provided in sections 324.400 to 324.439.
(L. 1998 H.B. 1601, et al. § 1, A.L. 2004 S.B. 1122, A.L. 2008 S.B. 788)
